N2  - The author comments on the article ?Downsizing in a Learning Organization: Are There Hidden Costs?? He states that the article is similar to a prior article but adds the insight that the level of disruption within an organization may be a function of the learning network's size before downsizing began. He comments on the authors suggesting that mapping technology can be utilized in identifying barriers to communication and help managers identify networks or individuals that create barriers to organizational performance and learning. He states he has three concerns concerning the use of network mapping technologies, including the fact there is no evidence provided that the technologies are valid methods for identifying contributing or detracting employees.
